Identify numeric or time fields.

Convert into list or pandas.DataFrame.

Choose visualization type:

Line â†’ trends (temperature, prices)

Bar â†’ comparison (rain per day)

Scatter â†’ correlation (temp vs humidity)

Pie â†’ proportion (category breakdown)

ğŸ’¡ Pro Tip

If youâ€™re unsure whatâ€™s inside your JSON, use this quick helper:

import json
def explore_json(data, level=0):
    indent = "  " * level
    if isinstance(data, dict):
        for key, value in data.items():
            print(f"{indent}- {key}: {type(value).__name__}")
            explore_json(value, level + 1)
    elif isinstance(data, list) and len(data) > 0:
        print(f"{indent}[List of {len(data)} â†’ {type(data[0]).__name__}]")
        explore_json(data[0], level + 1)

# Example:
explore_json(data)


