Red bar â†’ Maximum temperature (Â°C)

Green bar â†’ Average temperature (Â°C)

Blue bar â†’ Minimum temperature (Â°C)

ğŸ“Š What the Chart Shows
Element	Meaning
X-axis (horizontal)	Dates (each forecast day, e.g., 2025-10-21, 2025-10-22, â€¦)
Y-axis (vertical)	Temperature values in degrees Celsius (Â°C)
Bars	Three grouped bars per date â€” showing max, avg, and min temperatures
Title	"Temperature Forecast for <location>" â€” e.g., â€œTemperature Forecast for Perthâ€
Legend	Explains which color represents which temperature type
Gridlines	Horizontal dashed lines (--) to make temperature differences clearer
ğŸ§  Purpose of This Visualization

To compare temperature variations (max, min, avg) across multiple days.

To help identify trends (e.g., warming, cooling, or stable conditions).

To make it easy to see daily temperature ranges at a glance.

